                     <interp inst="t18280529-162-person931" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I went and took the prisoner - he told me the handkerchief was at an old clothes shop, in Charlton-street, Fitzroy-square - I found it there; the prisoner is my brother-in-law; I never knew him guilty of such a thing before.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was out of work and starving - I sold the handkerchief, but did not mean to steal it.</p>
